headlines.description: — Joel Embiid scored 32 points, James Harden had 24 points and 13 assists and the Philadelphia 76ers beat the Dallas Mavericks 111-101 on Friday night.

events.name: Washington Wizards at New York Knicks

headlines.description: — Julius Randle scored 18 points and grabbed 17 rebounds, RJ Barrett had 18 points and the New York Knicks outlasted the Washington Wizards 100-97 on Friday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Randle, Barrett help Knicks hold on to beat Wizards 100-97

events.name: Los Angeles Lakers at Toronto Raptors

headlines.description: — LeBron James scored 19 of his 36 points in the fourth quarter and overtime, Russell Westbrook had 22 points, 10 rebounds, and 10 assists, and the Los Angeles Lakers snapped a three-game losing streak by beating the Toronto Raptors 128-123 on Friday...
headlines.shortLinkText: James scores 35, Lakers beat Raptors in OT, snap 3-game skid

headlines.description: — Bogdan Bogdanovic scored a season-high 30 points, Delon Wright had 18 and the Atlanta Hawks beat the Memphis Grizzlies 120-105 on Friday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Bogdanovic scores 30 as Hawks beat Morant, Grizzlies 120-105

events.name: Portland Trail Blazers at Brooklyn Nets

headlines.description: — Seth Curry came back and some of the burden on Kevin Durant went away.
headlines.shortLinkText: Durant, Curry lead Nets back to beat Trail Blazers 128-123

headlines.description: — Lauri Markkanen made the go-ahead 3-pointer with 29 seconds left in overtime and scored a season-high 31 points, leading the Cleveland Cavaliers to a 119-116 victory over Denver on Friday night that snapped the Nuggets’ franchise-record road winning...
headlines.shortLinkText: Cavs top Nuggets 119-116 in OT, end Denver's road win streak

events.name: Oklahoma City Thunder at Miami Heat

headlines.description: — Tyler Herro got through an ankle scare and scored 26 points, Duncan Robinson scored 19 points in 19 minutes and the Eastern Conference-leading Miami Heat topped the Oklahoma City Thunder 120-108 on Friday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Herro has 26 points, East-leading Heat beat Thunder 120-108

headlines.description: — Malcolm Brogdon scored 25 points and Goga Bitadze added 23, including two key baskets down the stretch, to help the Indiana Pacers beat the Houston Rockets 121-118 on Friday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Brogdon & Bitadze lead Pacers to 121-118 win over Rockets

events.name: New Orleans Pelicans at San Antonio Spurs

headlines.description: — C.J McCollum had 20 points and the New Orleans Pelicans strengthened their play-in hopes by beating the San Antonio Spurs 124-91 on Friday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Pelicans strengthen play-in hopes, beat Spurs 124-91

headlines.description: — Rudy Gobert had 19 points, 16 rebounds and two blocks, and Jared Butler set career highs with 21 points and seven assists to lead the Utah Jazz to a 121-92 victory over the Los Angeles Clippers on Friday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Gobert, Butler lead Jazz to 121-92 victory over Clippers

headlines.description: — Jayson Tatum made seven 3-pointers and scored 32 points, Jaylen Brown added 30 points and the Boston Celtics beat the Sacramento Kings for the second time this season, 126-97 on Friday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Tatum, Brown combine for 62, Celtics beat Kings 126-97

headlines.description: — As if the Phoenix Suns aren’t strong enough already, Deandre Ayton is adding some dimensions to his game.
headlines.shortLinkText: Suns rout Bulls, move closer to wrapping up top spot in NBA
